inscribed: In blue ink [part of artwork]: That Was All / The poet wrestles with "language" / And the "verbs" are more easily found / out as "grace" to exist in seclusion / To hear of the day / dream all  that is bad / Of what "they" saw, the train / Whistle heard thru [sic] the night / Mare of the purple clouds / The penalty to go into the path / Finder of the comforting moss, / Our flood would save us / Itself a debase from which / miracles come. / Gerard Malanga
